<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-060-972  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 060 972.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer andamp; Software News  Feb 20 1989 v7 n8 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SCSI the interface for heavy workload. (One of two articlesdebating Enhanced Small Device Interface and Small ComputerSystems Interface) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Houseman, Doug.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Choosing the right peripheral interface is a critical part ofconfiguring a computer system.andP;  If the user wants a very fast harddisk, a specialized interface such as the Enhanced Small DeviceInterface (ESDI) is the interface to choose.andP;  If the user wantsone interface that performs a lot of work and allows for modularcomputer configurations, the Small Computer Systems Interface(SCSI) is the interface to choose.andP;  Using SCSI also simplifiestraining of sales and support staff.andP;  SCSI is an easy interface toexplain to the customer.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Enhanced Small Device InterfaceInterfaceSystem DesignPeripheralsDisk DrivesSmall Computer Systems Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>